org.phlo.tuplez.operation
Interface StatementIsComputed<InputType>

Type Parameters:
InputType - Interface representing a database operation's input parameters
All Superinterfaces:
OperationInput<InputType>
public interface StatementIsComputed<InputType>
extends OperationInput<InputType>

Marks implementation of Operation as having a SQL statement which depends on the input parameter an can therefore not be specified by an annotation.

Implementations of Operation must provide a getStatement(InputType input) method.

The type passed as InputType here must be assignable from instances of the database operation's InputType.

See Also:
getStatement(Object)

Method Summary
 String getStatement(InputType input)
          Must return the statement to be used to execute an StatementIsComputed implementation
 

Method Detail

getStatement

String getStatement(InputType input)
Must return the statement to be used to execute an StatementIsComputed implementation

The returned statement can use parameter references to reference input values. The only substitutions which are supposed to be done in this method are ones for which normal parameter substitution is not sufficient. One could, for example, add different "ORDER BY" clauses to the statement depending on some input value.

Parameters:
input - the operation's input values
Returns:
the statement to be sent to the database.
